FuelTrack LK — Future Features & Roadmap
==========================================


================================================================================
 PHASE 1 — BACKEND INTEGRATION (Priority: Critical)
================================================================================

These features connect the existing frontend to Firebase and make the app
functional with real data instead of mock data.

1.1  Firebase Authentication Integration
     - Replace the mock login/logout with Firebase Auth
     - Email + password registration with email verification
     - Persist login sessions using AsyncStorage
     - Password reset via "Forgot your password?" link
     - Auto-login returning users (check auth state on app launch)
     - Secure logout that clears session tokens

1.2  Firebase Realtime Database Connection
     - Replace all mockData.js imports with live Firebase queries
     - Set up Firebase config and initialization in the app
     - Create data service layer (read/write functions per collection)
     - Real-time listeners for fuel availability changes
     - Real-time listeners for queue report updates
     - Offline data persistence using Firebase's built-in caching

1.3  Social Login
     - Google Sign-In integration (replace placeholder button)
     - Facebook Login integration (replace placeholder button)
     - Link social accounts with existing email accounts

1.4  Queue Report Submission
     - Connect ReportQueueScreen form to /queueReports collection
     - Submit queue level, fuel availability, and vehicle count to Firebase
     - Validate report data before submission
     - Rate-limit reports (one report per station per user per 15 minutes)
     - Update /fuelAvailability based on reported fuel stock
     - Update /stationQueueSummary with latest aggregated data

1.5  Push Notifications
     - Integrate Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)
     - Register device FCM token on login and store in user profile
     - Receive fuel supply arrival notifications
     - Receive queue change alerts for favorited stations
     - Receive fuel price update notifications
     - In-app notification feed (already built — connect to /notifications)
     - Notification preferences in Profile settings


================================================================================
 PHASE 2 — MAP & LOCATION FEATURES (Priority: High)
================================================================================

These features add real map functionality and GPS-based services.

2.1  Google Maps Integration
     - Replace the fake grid map on TrackQueueScreen with real Google Maps
     - Show all nearby fuel stations as pins on the map
     - Custom pin markers with fuel type and queue status colors
     - User's current location pin with blue dot
     - Tap pin → show station info popup → navigate to StationDetails

2.2  GPS Location Services
     - Replace hardcoded "Pita Kotte" with actual device location
     - Calculate real distances between user and each station
     - Sort stations by actual distance (not static distanceKm values)
     - Reverse geocoding to show readable location name in top bar
     - Request location permissions on first launch

2.3  Navigation & Directions
     - "Navigate" button opens turn-by-turn directions to station
     - Integration with Google Maps or Waze for external navigation
     - Show estimated driving time and distance on StationDetails
     - Route preview on TrackQueueScreen

2.4  Geofencing & Nearby Alerts
     - Alert user when they're near a station with short queues
     - Auto-suggest nearest station when fuel is likely needed
     - Background location tracking (battery optimized)


================================================================================
 PHASE 3 — FUEL EXPENSE TRACKING (Priority: High)
================================================================================

Personal fuel management features for drivers.

3.1  Fuel Purchase Logger
     - New "Add Expense" screen after refueling
     - Input fields: fuel type, liters, price per liter, total cost
     - Optional odometer reading for mileage tracking
     - Select station from nearby list or search
     - Auto-fill current fuel price from /fuelPrices

3.2  Spending Analytics Dashboard
     - Monthly fuel spending chart (bar or line graph)
     - Weekly spending breakdown
     - Spending by fuel type (pie chart)
     - Comparison with previous month/week
     - Average cost per kilometer calculation
     - Total liters consumed this month

3.3  Fuel Price Tracking
     - Display current fuel prices on Home screen
     - Price history graph (line chart over last 6 months)
     - Price change notifications when government updates prices
     - Price comparison (if different stations have different prices)


================================================================================
 PHASE 4 — AI & SMART FEATURES (Priority: Medium)
================================================================================

Intelligence features that make the app predictive and proactive.

4.1  Real AI Prediction Engine
     - Replace hardcoded prediction data with computed analytics
     - Analyze historical queue reports to find patterns
     - Predict busy hours for each station based on day of week and time
     - Calculate optimal visit times and display on PredictionsScreen
     - Confidence scores for predictions based on data volume
     - Firebase Cloud Functions for server-side computation

4.2  Smart Recommendations
     - "Best station right now" based on queue + distance + availability
     - "Best time to go" personalized to user's saved locations
     - Suggest alternative stations when primary choice has long queues
     - Weekend vs weekday pattern detection

4.3  Fuel Consumption Predictions
     - Predict when user will need to refuel based on usage patterns
     - "Low fuel reminder" based on estimated remaining range
     - Suggested refueling schedule optimization


================================================================================
 PHASE 5 — COMMUNITY & SOCIAL FEATURES (Priority: Medium)
================================================================================

Features that build a community of trusted reporters.

5.1  Report Verification System
     - Cross-validate reports from multiple users at same station
     - Show "verified by X drivers" badge on station queue status
     - Confidence score based on number of consistent reports
     - Flag and discard obviously incorrect reports

5.2  User Reputation System
     - Track reporting accuracy per user
     - Award badges for consistent and accurate reports
     - Show reputation level on profile (Bronze → Silver → Gold)
     - Higher-reputation users' reports weighted more heavily

5.3  Station Reviews & Ratings
     - Allow users to rate stations (1-5 stars)
     - Written reviews with text comments
     - Rate specific aspects: service, cleanliness, wait time accuracy
     - Review moderation by admin

5.4  Favorites & Watch List
     - Favorite button on StationDetails (replace placeholder heart icon)
     - "My Favorites" section on Profile or Home screen
     - Receive priority notifications for favorited stations
     - Quick access to favorited stations from Home


================================================================================
 PHASE 6 — ADMIN & MANAGEMENT (Priority: Medium)
================================================================================

Backend management features for administrators and station owners.

6.1  Admin Dashboard
     - Web-based or in-app admin panel
     - Add, edit, and remove fuel stations
     - Update fuel prices nationally
     - View all queue reports and flag suspicious activity
     - User management (ban, verify, assign roles)
     - System-wide notification broadcasting

6.2  Station Owner Portal
     - Station owners can update their own availability
     - Set opening/closing times
     - Mark fuel deliveries when supply arrives
     - View analytics for their station (visits, reports, ratings)

6.3  Data Analytics
     - Dashboard showing app-wide statistics
     - Most visited stations, busiest times, most reported stations
     - User growth metrics
     - Report volume trends


================================================================================
 PHASE 7 — POLISH & PRODUCTION (Priority: Low initially, Critical for launch)
================================================================================

Quality improvements needed before app store release.

7.1  Form Validation
     - Email format validation on SignUp and Login
     - Password strength requirements (min 8 chars, uppercase, number)
     - Confirm password match check on SignUp
     - Required field validation on all forms
     - Inline error messages with red text and shake animation

7.2  Loading & Error States
     - Skeleton screens while data loads from Firebase
     - Pull-to-refresh on station lists and notifications
     - Error boundary for crash handling
     - Network connectivity detection with offline banner
     - Retry buttons on failed requests

7.3  Onboarding Improvements
     - Multi-page onboarding with swipe carousel (currently single page)
     - Vehicle setup during onboarding
     - Location permission request during onboarding
     - Notification permission request during onboarding

7.4  Accessibility
     - Screen reader support with proper accessibility labels
     - Sufficient color contrast ratios
     - Touch target sizes minimum 44x44 points
     - Dynamic text scaling support

7.5  Performance Optimization
     - Image lazy loading and caching
     - FlatList with pagination for large station lists
     - Debounced search input
     - Memoized components with React.memo
     - Reduce re-renders with useCallback and useMemo

7.6  App Store Preparation
     - Production build configuration
     - Android APK/AAB generation
     - iOS IPA generation (requires Mac)
     - App store screenshots and descriptions
     - Privacy policy and terms of service
     - App icon finalization (already designed)
     - Splash screen configuration

7.7  Testing
     - Unit tests for utility functions and data transformations
     - Component tests for reusable components
     - Integration tests for navigation flows
     - End-to-end tests for critical user journeys
     - Firebase security rules testing


